HEADWORD: Prevenancy
<hw>Prev"e*nan*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
anticipating another's wishes, desires, etc., in the way of favor or
courtesy; hence, civility; obligingness.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sterne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

